readme:
Service Usage

This Service is used to load a visa into TRIPS. TRIPS processes the request to send back the applicant id (unique applicant identifier) together with success or failure message.

Service Behaviour

The consumer of this service provides the details that are required to call TRIPS. ESB performs transformation into TRIPS request which is a flat file and routes to TRIPS. Response from TRIPS which is a flat file is transformed into XML and returned to Consumer.

Service Variants

None

Service Dependencies

None

Service Composition

Service Flow

An event is generated by the Service Consumer which invokes the Store Visa service on the ESB;
ESB Validate the request message sent by the consumer
ESB transforms the consumer request into TRIPS request which is a flat file and sends to TRIPS
TRIPS returns response to the ESB
ESB transforms the TRIPS response to Consumer response and returns to consumer.
Alternate Flow 1 (AF1)
The following alternate service flow depicts the execution path that takes place when the primary provider raises an error.
ESB transforms Provider Error returned by TRIPS into Enterprise Error Message.
ESB returns response with Enterprise Error payload.

Transformation

See SV351v01.00Micro.xls

Service State Management Decisions

No state management required.
